current_task:
CRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS FOR MULTI-AGENT PARALLEL DEVELOPMENT:

1. Create ONLY ONE file: feature_list.json (in the project root)
2. Do NOT create any markdown files, docs, plans, or README files
3. Do NOT explain your reasoning - just write the JSON file

4. Use this EXACT flat JSON structure:
{
  "pending_backend": [
    {"name": "Feature Name", "description": "Brief description", "acceptance_criteria": ["criterion 1"], "depends_on": []}
  ],
  "pending_frontend": [
    {"name": "Feature Name", "description": "Brief description", "acceptance_criteria": ["criterion 1"], "depends_on": []}
  ],
  "completed_backend": [],
  "completed_frontend": []
}

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
⚠️  CRITICAL: INIT FEATURES MUST BE FIRST!
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
The FIRST feature for EACH agent type MUST be a project initialization feature.
All other features will WAIT until init features complete.

Required structure:
  Feature #1: {"name": "Initialize [Framework] Backend", "is_init": true, ...}
  Feature #2+: {"name": "User Auth", "depends_on": ["Initialize [Framework] Backend"], ...}

Examples of INIT features:
  - Backend: "Initialize NestJS App", "Setup Express Server", "Create FastAPI Project"
  - Frontend: "Setup React with Vite", "Initialize Next.js App", "Create Vue Project"

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
FEATURE STRUCTURE (with optional subtasks for parallel work):
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
{
  "name": "User Authentication",
  "id": "user-auth",  // Unique ID for dependency tracking
  "description": "Implement user login, registration, and session management",
  "is_init": false,  // true ONLY for first/setup features
  "depends_on": ["Initialize NestJS App"],  // Features that must complete first
  "acceptance_criteria": ["Users can register", "Users can login", "JWT tokens work"],
  "subtasks": [  // OPTIONAL: Split into parallel subtasks
    {
      "id": "auth-model",
      "description": "Create User entity and repository",
      "file_scope": ["backend/src/users/**", "backend/src/entities/user.*"],
      "depends_on": []
    },
    {
      "id": "auth-jwt",
      "description": "Implement JWT authentication strategy",
      "file_scope": ["backend/src/auth/**"],
      "depends_on": ["auth-model"]
    }
  ]
}

5. Create 3-5 features per agent type (backend, frontend)
6. Subtasks enable PARALLEL development - multiple agents can work on different subtasks
7. File scopes PREVENT CONFLICTS - agents only modify files in their scope
8. After writing feature_list.json, STOP IMMEDIATELY. Do NOT continue with any other work.
